headline: CME's Q2 beat, Lamb Weston's cost savings, Cal-Maine's Q4 beat

CME Group (CME) reported second quarter earnings results that were better than analysts expected. Lamb Weston (LW) stock is surging after the company reported a fourth quarter earnings beat. The company also announced a cost-savings plan, hoping to save at least $250 million annually by the end of 2028. Cal-Maine Foods (CALM) stock is also surging after the company delivered better-than-expected fourth quarter results. Stay up to date on the latest market action, minute-by-minute, with Yahoo Finance's Market Minute.

headline: Lamb Weston (NYSE:LW) Surprises With Q2 Sales, Stock Soars
summary: Potato products company Lamb Weston (NYSE:LW) reported Q2 CY2025 results exceeding the market’s revenue expectations, with sales up 4% year on year to $1.68 billion. The company’s full-year revenue guidance of $6.45 billion at the midpoint came in 0.7% above analysts’ estimates. Its non-GAAP profit of $0.87 per share was 38.2% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
